    "body": "> You will probably still need it.\n\nThe `files/` prefix should go away.  Simple relative URLs should work.  It will behave exactly the same as `files/path/to/img` works today, just without the leading `files`.  Note that absolute URLs (`/files/`) should never be used for this, even in 0.13.\n"
